spanishExample: Lo extrañas porque te quedaba bien.
englishTranslation: You miss it because it fit you well.

spanishExample: Si lo olvida, puede no despertarse a tiempo.
englishTranslation: If she forgets it, she might not wake up on time.

spanishExample: Me alegro de haberme ido.
englishTranslation: I’m really glad for having left.

spanishExample: A veces olvido que esto podría existir.
englishTranslation: Sometimes I forget that this could exist.

spanishExample: No olvides que yo siempre sueño con ello.
englishTranslation: Don’t forget that I always dream about it.

spanishExample: Mi amigo está triste por haberte visto.
englishTranslation: My friend is sad for having seen you.

spanishExample: Olvida que la entrada es a través de la puerta.
englishTranslation: She forgets that the entrance is via the door.

spanishExample: Pudiste habernos dicho eso.
englishTranslation: You could(preterite) have told us that.

spanishExample: Debí haberlo sabido.
englishTranslation: I should(Deber preterite) have known about it.

spanishExample: Desearía no haberlo soñado.
englishTranslation: I would wish not to have dreamt it.

spanishExample: Olvidó que no le queda bien.
englishTranslation: He forgot that it doesn’t fit her well.

spanishExample: Quiero que olvide haberte dado eso.
englishTranslation: I want her to forget having given you that.

spanishExample: Puede que olvides cómo llegar a la tienda.
englishTranslation: It might be that you forget how to get to the store.

spanishExample: No puedes olvidar cómo llegar a la estación, es a través de la calle.
englishTranslation: You can’t forget how to get to the station, it’s across the street

spanishExample: ¡No olvide que tiene que ir al mercado!
englishTranslation: (Formal) Don’t forget that you have to go to the market!

spanishExample: Quiere que olvide que está en la cárcel.
englishTranslation: She wants me to forget that she’s in jail.

spanishExample: Me alegra haberme ido.
englishTranslation: It makes me glad to have left.

spanishExample: ¡Olvídalo! Si no se despierta, no iremos a la iglesia.
englishTranslation: Forget it! If she doesn’t wake up, we won’t go to church.

spanishExample: Me despierto temprano porque el reloj existe.
englishTranslation: I wake up early because the clock exists.

spanishExample: Comió después de haberse quedado.
englishTranslation: She ate after having stayed.

spanishExample: Extraño ese restaurante ahora que estoy en prisión.
englishTranslation: I miss that restaurant now that I’m in prison.

spanishExample: No están aquí, debes haberlos soñado.
englishTranslation: They aren’t here, you must(Deber present) have dreamt them.

spanishExample: Se fue del colegio sin haberlo hecho.
englishTranslation: She left school without having done it.

spanishExample: Está en problemas por haberle dicho.
englishTranslation: He is in trouble for having told her.

spanishExample: Olvídate del bar, necesitamos ir al banco.
englishTranslation: Forget about the bar, we need to go to the bank.
